The paper focuses on data collection for robotic manipulation, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) category. The use of human supervision and reasoning to collect high-quality data suggests a potential overlap with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The mention of computer vision (cs.CV) in the abstract also suggests a potential focus on visual perception for manipulation tasks. Finally, the evaluation of the platform's utility through quantitative and qualitative analysis suggests a potential overlap with human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
